> Those who perform homam can make offering to other celestial beings, deities and masters not mentioned in the manuals, if they want. These are OPTIONAL. I will write them so that those who want to use them can use them. You can pick one or more based on your inclination. Instead of doing many, it is good to pick one or a few that you are really attached to and do them with devotion.
>
>
>
> Yakshas: [supernatural beings of wealth and magic]
>
> OM yakShebhyaH svaahaa, yaKShebya idaM na mama
>
> Kinnaras: [supernatural beings of pleasure]
>
> OM kinnarebhyaH svaahaa, kinnarebya idaM na mama
>
> Gandharvas: [supernatural beings excelling in music]
>
> OM gandharvebhyaH svaahaa, gandharvebhya idaM na mama
>
> Apsaras: [celstial nymphs excelling in dance]
>
> OM apsaraabhyaH svaahaa, apsaraabhya idaM na mama
>
> Siddhas: [perfected beings with miraculous abilities]
>
> OM siddhebhyaH svaahaa, siddhebhya idaM na mama
>
> Vidyadharas: [supernatural beings of yogic knowledge and miraculous abilities]
>
> OM vidyaadharebhyaH svaahaa, vidyaadharebhya idaM na mama
>
> Nathas: [perfected beings with Narayana's amsha, who come together to earth in different forms to establish Dharmik Order on earth from time to time]
>
> OM naathebhyaH svaahaa, naathebhya idaM na mama
>
> Munis: [An inward-turned sage often in *true* silence of mind, i.e. not just external silence]
>
> OM munibhyaH svaahaa, munibhya idaM na mama
>
> Rishis: [A seer who simply flows with divine will - Rish means to flow]
>
> OM R^iShibhyaH svaahaa, R^iShibhya idaM na mama
>
> Indra: [A Vedic deity who leads gods]
>
> OM indraaya svaahaa, indraayedaM na mama
>
> Mitra: [A Vedic deity who holds together the objects in duality]
>
> OM mitraaya svaahaa, mitraayedaM na mama
>
> Varuna: [A Vedic deity who holds the duality together]
>
> OM varuNaaya svaahaa, varuNaayedaM na mama
>
> Agni: [A Vedic deity who takes back from duality to non-duality]
>
> OM agnaye svaahaa, agnaya na mama
>
> Soma: [A Vedic deity who enhances one's experience of the field of duality]
>
> OM somaaya svaahaa, somaayedaM na mama
>
> Vaayu: [A Vedic deity who causes movement in consciousness, so that it experiences duality]
>
> OM vaayave svaahaa, vaayava idaM na mama
>
> Surya: [A Vedic deity who sustains the "One Truth" behind consciousness]
>
> OM sUryaaya svaahaa, sUryaayedaM na mama
>
> Bhaga: []
>
> OM bhagaaya svaahaa, bhagaayedaM na mama
>
> Pushan: []
>
> OM pUShNe svaahaa, pUShNa idaM na mama
>
> Aryaman: []
>
> OM aryamNe svaahaa, aryamNa idaM na mama
